These recalls are equally, if not more, disturbing, since the campaigns went well beyond the local districts and involved national gun control and gun rights lobbies. Nationalizing local races has a detrimental impact on democracy, since it takes power away from the voters and constituents who actually have to live with the decisions made by the state lawmakers. And it's bad for democracy, too, since it puts elected officials all over the country on notice: vote our way or you may not survive another week. Such a constant threat prevents lawmakers of any ideological stripe from making reasoned, responsible decisions. It used to be that lawmakers went into campaign mode a few months before the election. Then, elected officials went into almost constant campaign mode, always aware of the effect their votes would have on their next elections.
